version: 1
rules:
  - name: "Project Overview"
    description: |
      This is a reusable e-commerce monorepo project:
      - apps/api (NestJS)
      - apps/dashboard (ReactJS + Tailwind + ShadCN)
      - apps/landing (Vite + Tailwind)
      - packages/ui and packages/utils are shared components and helpers.
    appliesTo: ["*"]

  - name: "Coding Guidelines"
    description: |
      - Use TypeScript for all code files.
      - Follow ESLint and Prettier standards.
      - Prefer functional components and hooks over class components.
      - Use TailwindCSS utility classes instead of inline styles.
      - In NestJS, each module must have: controller, service, dto, entity.
    appliesTo: ["*.ts", "*.tsx"]

  - name: "File Naming"
    description: |
      - Use PascalCase for React components.
      - Use camelCase for hooks, utils, and variables.
      - Avoid files longer than 500 lines. Split into smaller files if necessary.
    appliesTo: ["*.ts", "*.tsx"]

  - name: "Commenting Rules"
    description: |
      - All comments in the source code must be written in clear, concise English.
      - Avoid adding unnecessary or irrelevant comments.
      - Only add comments when explaining complex logic, non-obvious behavior, or TODOs.
      - Do not add automatic or generic comments (e.g., 'this is a function').
    appliesTo: ["*.ts", "*.tsx", "*.js", "*.jsx"]